         <abstract>
            <p>The degenerate parabolic equation $$\frac{\partial u}{\partial t} = \nabla \cdot (|u|^\nu\nabla u), \nu \geqslant 1,$$ has been used to model the flow of gas through a porous medium. Error estimates for continuous and discrete time finite element procedures to approximate the solution of this equation are proved, and several new regularity results are given.</p>
          </abstract>
